This paper is about learning a semantic parser with less supervised training data using question generation, which is a common technique in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). The paper specifically focuses on the WikiSQL dataset, which is a large hand-annotated semantic parsing dataset. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and ML. The paper also involves neural networks, which are a common tool in AI (Artificial Intelligence), making cs.AI another likely sub-category. The paper deals with SQL queries, which are commonly used in databases, making cs.DB a possible sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning models and accuracy, which are common topics in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
